# Cursor Rules for IQ LDS Project

## Documentation Maintenance

### Critical Rule: Always Update Documentation
When making changes to patterns, design system, components, or layouts, **MUST** update the corresponding documentation:

- **Pattern Changes**: Update `docs/page-layouts.md` or `docs/creating-pages.md`
- **Design System Changes**: Update `docs/design-system.md` (colors, typography, spacing, etc.)
- **Component Changes**: Update `docs/components.md` or `COMPONENTS.md`
- **New Patterns**: Create new documentation or update existing docs

### Documentation Update Checklist
Before committing changes that affect UI/UX:
- [ ] Updated relevant documentation files
- [ ] Added code examples if introducing new patterns
- [ ] Updated examples if patterns changed
- [ ] Verified documentation accuracy

## Design System

### Design Tokens
- Use CSS variables for theming (defined in `src/index.css`)
- Follow the spacing scale: multiples of 4px (space-1 through space-16)
- Use semantic color names: `primary`, `secondary`, `muted`, `destructive`
- Maintain consistent border radius: `rounded-md` (6px) for most components

### Color System
- Base color: `neutral` (from components.json)
- Use `cssVariables: true` for theme support
- Dark mode: Automatically handled via CSS variables
- Never hardcode colors - always use design tokens

### Typography
- Default font: System UI fonts
- Font sizes: Use Tailwind scale (text-xs through text-4xl)
- Font weights: `font-normal` (400), `font-medium` (500), `font-semibold` (600), `font-bold` (700)
- Line heights: Use default Tailwind line heights

### Spacing
- Page padding: `py-8` or `py-12` for vertical spacing
- Section spacing: `space-y-6` or `space-y-8` between sections
- Container padding: `px-4` or `px-6` for horizontal padding
- Gap: Use `gap-{size}` for flex/grid layouts

## Component Usage

### Component Library
- Use shadcn/ui components from `@/components/ui`
- Style: `radix-nova` (from components.json)
- Icon library: `lucide` (from components.json)
- Import path: `@/components/ui/{component-name}`

### Component Patterns
- Prefer composition over configuration
- Use component variants when available
- Extend components rather than creating new ones
- Maintain accessibility (ARIA labels, semantic HTML)

### Component File Structure
- Components in `src/components/ui/`
- Use TypeScript with `.tsx` extension
- Export all component parts (e.g., Card, CardHeader, CardContent)

## Page Creation

### Page Structure
- Place pages in appropriate routing directory
- Use semantic HTML (`<main>`, `<section>`, `<article>`)
- Include proper page structure:
  ```tsx
  <div className="container mx-auto py-8">
    <h1>Page Title</h1>
    {/* Content */}
  </div>
  ```

### Layout Patterns
- **Container Layout**: Use `container mx-auto` for centered content
- **Full-Width**: Use `w-full` for full-width layouts
- **Grid**: Use `grid` with responsive columns
- **Flex**: Use `flex` for flexible arrangements
- **Sidebar**: Use Sidebar component for navigation layouts

### Responsive Design
- Mobile-first approach
- Use Tailwind breakpoints: `sm`, `md`, `lg`, `xl`, `2xl`
- Test on multiple screen sizes
- Ensure touch targets are at least 44x44px

## Code Style

### TypeScript
- Use TypeScript for all components
- Define proper types and interfaces
- Use `React.ComponentProps` for component prop types
- Avoid `any` types

### React Patterns
- Use functional components with hooks
- Prefer named exports for components
- Use `cn()` utility for className merging
- Handle loading and error states

### File Naming
- Components: `kebab-case.tsx` (e.g., `button-group.tsx`)
- Pages: `PascalCase.tsx` (e.g., `HomePage.tsx`)
- Utilities: `kebab-case.ts` (e.g., `format-date.ts`)

### Import Organization
```tsx
// 1. React imports
import * as React from "react"

// 2. Third-party imports
import { Component } from "library"

// 3. Internal imports - UI components
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"

// 4. Internal imports - Utilities
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"

// 5. Internal imports - Types
import type { ComponentProps } from "@/types"
```

## Path Aliases
Use the configured path aliases from `components.json`:
- `@/components` - Components directory
- `@/components/ui` - UI components
- `@/lib` - Utility functions
- `@/lib/utils` - Utility functions (cn, etc.)
- `@/hooks` - Custom React hooks

## Accessibility

### Requirements
- All interactive elements must be keyboard accessible
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Include ARIA labels where needed
- Ensure color contrast meets WCAG AA standards
- Test with screen readers

### ARIA Patterns
- Use `aria-label` for icon-only buttons
- Use `aria-describedby` for form field descriptions
- Use `role` attributes when semantic HTML isn't sufficient
- Manage focus states properly

## Performance

### Best Practices
- Lazy load heavy components
- Optimize images (use next/image if available)
- Minimize bundle size
- Use React.memo for expensive components
- Avoid unnecessary re-renders

## Testing

### Component Testing
- Test component rendering
- Test user interactions
- Test accessibility
- Test responsive behavior

## Git Workflow

### Commit Messages
When committing documentation updates:
- Format: `docs: {description}` for documentation changes
- Format: `feat: {description}` for new features with docs
- Format: `fix: {description}` for bug fixes with docs

### Documentation Changes
- Always update docs in the same commit as code changes
- Include examples when adding new patterns
- Update related documentation files
- Verify links and references

## Design Decisions

### When to Update Documentation
Update documentation when:
- Adding new layout patterns
- Changing design tokens (colors, spacing, typography)
- Introducing new component patterns
- Modifying existing patterns
- Adding new design guidelines
- Changing accessibility requirements

### Documentation Files
- `docs/README.md` - Documentation index
- `docs/creating-pages.md` - Page creation guide
- `docs/page-layouts.md` - Layout patterns
- `docs/components.md` - Component usage
- `docs/design-system.md` - Design tokens and guidelines
- `COMPONENTS.md` - Component installation list

## Reminders

### Before Making UI Changes
1. Check existing patterns in documentation
2. Review design system guidelines
3. Ensure consistency with existing code
4. Plan documentation updates

### After Making UI Changes
1. Update relevant documentation
2. Add/update code examples
3. Verify documentation accuracy
4. Update related documentation files
5. Check for broken links or references

